707341f-a.text:
West End Ave., east side, between Hampton Ave., and Oriental Boulevard (street is in the background). The frame house to the left of the right of way in the background, is No. 120 West End Ave. The Long Island R.R. right of way is also seen. This area comprises 12 acres, vhich extends north from Brighton Beach through to Neptune Aves, with frontage on Shore Ave. Upon this site ~hich is near a fully developed community will be erected apartments and stores. For further information see the New York Sun,
February 11, 1937.
December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
